reviews.reviewText: I got my son these light up bath dinosaurs and he loves them! They’re actually so cute, they light up when water touches them and go back off when they are dry. My son loves playing with them in the bath!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Makes bath and bedtimes lots more fun!
reviews.reviewText: Solid little dinosaur have bright, color changing lights inside! Our 3 & 6 year old gransons love them! They learned that if they lick their finger they can keep them lit up in bed as night lights too. The batteries last a long time, but (I guess for safety reasons) you can’t open them to change the battery.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Who Doesn't Want Glowing Dinosaurs In The Tub??
reviews.reviewText: These have been all over social media, and I was stoked to get them when we needed new bath toys. I had my eyes on some other ones promoted by influencers, but when researching and finding dino versions - I knew we had a winner!I was curious to know how these worked when I decided to get them and was worried it would use batteries or electronics, which I don't want in the water, but I figured they are sold as bath toys and work for everyone else. However, I was excited to see metal conduits on the bottom of the dinosaurs that activate the light when they come in contact with water! What an excellent opportunity to teach our kids about STEM!They are durable, adorable, and bright! We can see the light in them whether we have the bathroom lights on or dimmed/off. We like to combine these with our bath building blocks and create little houses for the dinos - which our toddler then successfully destroys with his dino, and we repeat that process!It is a successful product and an item our toddler consistently reaches for! We will be getting more of these in the future!
